snippet.textDisplay:
Mate i could right a massive essay to you right now on how much i agree with you but i think you already know it. Gotta be honest too, ive been in a really shitty state of mind for the past couple years too. Its actually somewhat surreal to hear you say what you say because its exactly how i think. Unfortunately i dont have the followers or friends or anything like that, so when things get bad for me they are just bad and i have no choice but to push through it. Im 26, i live in the shittest 1 bedroom unit and just hide in here on my PC when im not at work. The only contact i have with humans is either at work with my boss or sitting here watching people. Its fucking terrible and i hate it everyday dude honestly. Its absolutely fucked. But all i can say that gets me through everytime is "it could be worse". I could have been born and given away at birth to live an extremely poverty stricken life, or be born with a severe disability, many things that could have happened that made it worse, but im still here my heart is still beating and my brain still has the ability to help people and thats all that matters. Keep your head up mate, and if you ever happen to pass through Albury NSW id happily buy ya a beer and a chat. Cheers (y)
